        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the special tools, remove and discard the front pump seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010275" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0018747.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the front pump stator support seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010276" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0006626.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the 2 seals.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010277" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057627.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the pump outer diameter square-cut front pump seal.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010278" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057636.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Note the location of the bolts for assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the overdrive piston return spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010279" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057637.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and discard the overdrive piston.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010280" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057638.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts and separate the pump control body from the pump body.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010281" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057639.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the pump gears or plate show any signs of wear or scoring, a new pump assembly must be
                    installed.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and inspect the plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010282" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057640.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not remove any of the cup plugs unless directed to do so in other steps. Do not remove the
                    stator support from the control body. This can distort the surface of the control body.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the converter clutch control valve, cooler bypass valve and thermostat valve,
                converter pressure limit valve, converter anti-drain back valve and the main regulator valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010283" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0066469.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the retainer clip with a small screwdriver, then remove the main
                    regulator plug, spring and valve.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the retainer clip with a small screwdriver, then remove the converter
                    anti-drain back plug, spring and valve.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the retainer clip with a small screwdriver, then remove the converter
                    pressure limit plug, spring and valve.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the retainer clip with a small screwdriver, then remove thermostat plug,
                    spring and valve.
                </callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the cooler bypass valve.</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Remove the retainer clip with a small magnet or pliers, then remove the
                    converter clutch control plug with shuttle valve, spring retainer and valve.
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid part damage and loss of function, do not clean the pump thermostat with mineral spirits
                    or solvent.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove and inspect the inner and the outer gearotor gears.</para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Clean all pump parts except the thermostat, in solvent.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Dry the parts with compressed air.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Inspect the pump gears, faces, gear teeth, pump housing and mating surfaces for damage or
                    scoring.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>If any parts are damaged or worn, install a new pump.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <figure id="f07010284" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0066470.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the converter hub bushing. If scored or excessively worn, install a new pump. Note
                the orientation of the notch in the bushing. It must face up.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010285" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0029438.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the front input shaft bushing. If the bushing is worn or scored, install a new
                pump.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010286" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0005660.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the rear input shaft bushing for wear. If scored or worn, install a new pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010287" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057641.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the following:</para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>All valve and plug bores for scoring or damage.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>All passages for obstructions.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Mating surfaces for burrs and scoring.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>All springs for distortion.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>When dry, check all valves and plugs for free movement in their respective bores.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
